Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I select C0 to Os coccygis vertebras on the localizer of Page 01
And	I go to Page 06 of Spine MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Pathology of the vertebral arch' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And Localizer is enabled
And 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled
And 'On both sides' radio button is enabled

And 'Retrosomatic interruption' radio button is enabled
And 'Pediculolysis' radio button is enabled
And 'Spondylolysis' radio button is enabled
And 'Retroisthmic interruption' radio button is enabled
And 'Paraspinosus interruption' radio button is enabled
And 'Spina bifida occulta' radio button is enabled


When I click on the Localizer
Then the localizer canvas opens
And C0 to Os coccygis vertebras are active and enabled

When I click on T1
Then T1 vertebra is selected and turns red

When I click on T4
Then T4 vertebra is selected and turns red
And T1 remains selected.


When I select 'Pediculolysis' radio button
Then 'Grade 0: No bone marrow edema, no cortical interruption' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade 1: Bone marrow edema, no Cortical interruption' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade 2: Incomplete fracture, Cortical interruption & bone marrow edema' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade 3: Complete fracture, cortical interruption & bone marrow edema' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade 4: Complete fracture/ "non-union" without bone marrow edeema' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Grade 2: Incomplete fracture, Cortical interruption & bone marrow edema' radio button
Then 'Location: Inferior cortex' checkbox is enabled
And 'Deep fracture line' checkbox is enabled
And '(Measurement in mm from the inferior cortex)' input field is enabled

When I select 'Grade 3: Complete fracture, cortical interruption & bone marrow edema' radio button
Then 'Oblique sagittal fracture line' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Spondylolysis' radio button
Then 'Grade 0: No bone marrow edema, no cortical interruption' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade 1: Bone marrow edema, no Cortical interruption' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade 2: Incomplete fracture, Cortical interruption & bone marrow edema' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade 3: Complete fracture, cortical interruption & bone marrow edema' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade 4: Complete fracture/ "non-union" without bone marrow edeema' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Grade 2: Incomplete fracture, Cortical interruption & bone marrow edema' radio button
Then 'Location: Inferior cortex' checkbox is enabled
And 'Deep fracture line' checkbox is enabled
And '(Measurement in mm from the inferior cortex)' input field is enabled

When I select 'Grade 3: Complete fracture, cortical interruption & bone marrow edema' radio button
Then 'Oblique sagittal fracture line' checkbox is enabled
